10/08/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Sali Berisha told Voice of America Thursday (August 9th) that independence is the only solution for Kosovo that would ensure regional stability. 
Berisha expressed support for the new negotiations between Belgrade and Pristina, while adding that further postponement of supervised independence is dangerous. 
(Shekulli, Shqip - 10/08/07; VOA - 09/08/07)
